.TH "radeon_vm_fence_pts" 9 "radeon_vm_fence_pts" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
radeon_vm_fence_pts \- fence page tables after an update
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" radeon_vm_fence_pts
.BI "(struct radeon_vm *vm "  ","
.BI "uint64_t start "  ","
.BI "uint64_t end "  ","
.BI "struct radeon_fence *fence "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vm" 12
requested vm
.IP "start" 12
start of GPU address range
.IP "end" 12
end of GPU address range
.IP "fence" 12
fence to use
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Fence the page tables in the range \fIstart\fP - \fIend\fP (cayman+).

Global and local mutex must be locked!
